[[File:Foliated dish with underglaze blue design of melons, bamboo and grapes, Jingdezhen ware, Yuan, 1271-1368, Shanghai Museum.jpg|thumb|[[Jingdezhen]]-ware, [[Yuan Dynasty]], 1271-1368]] [[File:Chu Ta 003.jpg|thumb|[[Bada Shanren]], 1626—1705]]
The '''culture of Jiangxi''' refers to the culture of the people based in [[Jiangxi]].<ref>许怀林. "江西历史文化特征概说." 江西广播电视大学学报 2 (1999): 37-41.</ref> It has changed greatly over several millenniums, from the land's prehistoric period to its contemporary culture, which incorporates ancient and traditional Chinese culture and modern culture influenced by [[Western culture]].
Geographic situation makes Jiangxi distinguish from its neighbours, as high mountains separate it from [[Zhejiang]] to the east, [[Fujian]] and [[Guangdong]] to the south, [[Hunan]] to the west and [[Yangzi River]] forms a natural division between the South and northern China.
==Language== {{Main|Gan Chinese}} Gan Chinese has always played a significant role in Jiangxi culture. The [[varieties of Chinese|Chinese variety]] is spoken mainly in Jiangxi but also in surrounding regions such as [[Hunan]], [[Hubei]], [[Anhui]], and [[Fujian]]. Modern Gan is considered as one of [[Sinitic languages]], which [[History of Gan Chinese|derives from Old Gan]] and still keeps some linguistic traces of ancient languages in [[Northern and southern China|South China]].
Gan Chinese is written in traditional [[Chinese characters]] with Gan variants. Many vocabulary items are no longer used in most Chinese varieties, particularly in Mandarin, while they remain in daily usage in Gan. For example, cooking utensils are called ''[[Wok|uoh]]'' (鑊) or ''[[Ding (vessel)|tiang]]'' (鼎) in Gan which date back to the [[Shang Dynasty]]. The [[Bible]] was also translated into [[List of Chinese Bible translations#Gan Chinese|some Gan dialects]] as the Christianity was introduced into Jiangxi as early as the 16th century, with the arrival of [[Marco Polo]].
==Academy culture== Since the academy represents the historical and cultural progress in a place, the importance of it gradually increased during the thousands of years in China. In ancient China, Jiangxi had four famous academies and they brought special learning atmosphere to Jiangxi for more than 2000 years.<ref>The academy culture in Jiangxi. Retrieved February 22, 2018, from http://www.lushantravel.com/Jiangxi%20Culture_%E6%B1%9F%E8%A5%BF%E6%96%87%E5%8C%96.html</ref>
==Tea culture== Tea is one of the most famous drink in the world; as a national drink in China, it represents not only the property of drinker but also the inspiration and tradition within the tea. Lushan Yunwu tea, which is named for Lushan Mountain in Jiangxi Province, shows the optimistic and peaceful character of people in Jiangxi.<ref>Zeng Tian. <<文化·大家>> 第34期：江西书院小史</ref>
==Literature== {{Main|Literature of Jiangxi}}
===Novel===
====Long==== Most of the long novels of Jiangxi don't show how reality is, they pay attention to the "excavation of history and culture".<ref>2016年江西文学观察. Retrieved February 27, 2018, from http://jx.ifeng.com/a/20170804/5883009_0.shtml</ref>
====Short story==== Different from the novels, the majority of short stories of Jiangxi closely related to the practice world. Urbanization beings several topics for writers to discuss how it changes and reforms the structure of society. In addition, the transformation process where traditional concepts are influenced by industrialization is shown in the short stories.<ref>2016年江西文学观察. Retrieved February 27, 2018, from http://jx.ifeng.com/a/20170804/5883009_0.shtml</ref>
